HEADWORD: Aiguille
<hw>Ai`guille"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., a
needle. See <er>Aglet</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A needle-shaped
peak.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An instrument for boring holes, used in
blasting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Aiguillette</ent>⟦br⟧
